<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-20065] Accord&apos;s ConfigService lock is held over large areas which cause deadlocks and performance issues</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-20065</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Accord has a AbstractConfigurationService that locks on &#8220;this&#8221; and does this over large ares, even when the lock is not needed.  This has been found to cause issues as messaging gets blocked on this causing timeouts.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To better improve things, we should lower the locking to what is needed and avoid locking while triggering callbacks&lt;/p&gt;</description>
